# Locators

Playwright recommends semantic locators for resilient tests.

```javascript
// Fill form fields
await page.getByLabel('User Name').fill('John');
await page.getByLabel('Password').fill('secret-password');

// Click button by role
await page.getByRole('button', { name: 'Sign in' }).click();

// Assert text
await expect(page.getByText('Welcome, John!')).toBeVisible();
```

Locator methods (preferred order):
1. `getByRole(role, { name })` - ARIA role + accessible name
2. `getByText(text)` - visible text content
3. `getByLabel(text)` - form label association
4. `getByPlaceholder(text)` - input placeholder
5. `getByTestId(id)` - data-testid attribute
6. `locator(selector)` - CSS/XPath fallback

Chaining: `page.getByRole('listitem').filter({ hasText: 'Product 2' })`
Combining: `locator1.or(locator2)`, `locator1.and(locator2)`

**Category:** Core
**URL:** https://playwright.dev/docs/locators

# Assertions

Playwright assertions auto-retry until condition is met or timeout.

```javascript
// Visibility
await expect(page.getByText('Welcome')).toBeVisible();
await expect(page.getByTestId('todo-item').first()).toBeVisible();

// Either/or visibility
await expect(
  page.getByRole('button', { name: 'Sign in' })
    .or(page.getByRole('button', { name: 'Sign up' }))
    .first()
).toBeVisible();

// Text content
await expect(page.getByRole('heading')).toHaveText('Welcome');

// Count
await expect(page.getByRole('listitem')).toHaveCount(3);

// URL
await expect(page).toHaveURL(/dashboard/);

// Title
await expect(page).toHaveTitle(/My App/);
```

Common assertions: toBeVisible(), toBeHidden(), toBeEnabled(), toBeDisabled(), toBeChecked(), toHaveText(), toHaveValue(), toHaveAttribute(), toHaveCount(), toContainText(), toHaveURL(), toHaveTitle().

All accept optional { timeout } parameter.

**Category:** Core
**URL:** https://playwright.dev/docs/api/class-locatorassertions

# Page Object Model

Encapsulate page interactions in classes.

```typescript
import type { Page, Locator } from '@playwright/test';

export class TodoPage {
  private readonly inputBox: Locator;
  private readonly todoItems: Locator;

  constructor(public readonly page: Page) {
    this.inputBox = this.page.locator('input.new-todo');
    this.todoItems = this.page.getByTestId('todo-item');
  }

  async goto() {
    await this.page.goto('https://demo.playwright.dev/todomvc/');
  }

  async addToDo(text: string) {
    await this.inputBox.fill(text);
    await this.inputBox.press('Enter');
  }

  async remove(text: string) {
    const todo = this.todoItems.filter({ hasText: text });
    await todo.hover();
    await todo.getByLabel('Delete').click();
  }
}
```

Best practice: One POM class per page/component. Use locators in constructor, actions as methods.

**Category:** Patterns
**URL:** https://playwright.dev/docs/test-fixtures

# API Mocking

Mock API responses to test without real backends.

```javascript
// Mock entire response
test('mocks API', async ({ page }) => {
  await page.route('*/**/api/v1/fruits', async route => {
    const json = [{ name: 'Strawberry', id: 21 }];
    await route.fulfill({ json });
  });
  await page.goto('https://demo.playwright.dev/api-mocking');
  await expect(page.getByText('Strawberry')).toBeVisible();
});

// Modify real response
test('modifies API response', async ({ page }) => {
  await page.route('*/**/api/v1/fruits', async route => {
    const response = await route.fetch();
    const json = await response.json();
    json.push({ name: 'Loquat', id: 100 });
    await route.fulfill({ response, json });
  });
  await page.goto('https://demo.playwright.dev/api-mocking');
});

// HAR replay
await page.routeFromHAR('./hars/fruit.har', {
  url: '*/**/api/v1/fruits',
  update: false,
});

// WebSocket mocking
await page.routeWebSocket('wss://example.com/ws', ws => {
  ws.onMessage(message => {
    if (message === 'request') ws.send('response');
  });
});
```

**Category:** Features
**URL:** https://playwright.dev/docs/mock

# Test Configuration

Configure Playwright tests with defineConfig.

```javascript
import {defineConfig, devices} from '@playwright/test';

export default defineConfig({
  testDir: 'tests',
  fullyParallel: true,
  forbidOnly: !!process.env.CI,
  retries: process.env.CI ? 2 : 0,
  workers: process.env.CI ? 1 : undefined,
  reporter: 'html',
  use: {
    baseURL: 'http://localhost:3000',
    trace: 'on-first-retry',
  },
  projects: [
    {
      name: 'chromium',
      use: {...devices['Desktop Chrome']},
    },
  ],
  webServer: {
    command: 'npm run start',
    url: 'http://localhost:3000',
    reuseExistingServer: !process.env.CI,
  },
});
```

Top-level options: testDir, fullyParallel, forbidOnly, retries, workers, reporter, timeout, globalSetup, globalTeardown. use options: baseURL, trace, screenshot, video, viewport. projects: run tests on multiple browsers. webServer: auto-start dev server before tests.

**Category:** Configuration
**URL:** https://playwright.dev/docs/test-configuration

# Worker-Scoped Fixtures

Create fixtures that initialize once per worker process.

```typescript
import {test as base, expect} from '@playwright/test';

type Account = {username: string; password: string};

export const test = base.extend<{}, {account: Account}>({
  account: [async ({browser}, use, workerInfo) => {
    const username = 'user' + workerInfo.workerIndex;
    const password = 'verysecure';
    const page = await browser.newPage();
    await page.goto('/signup');
    await page.getByLabel('User Name').fill(username);
    await page.getByLabel('Password').fill(password);
    await page.getByText('Sign up').click();
    await expect(page.getByTestId('result')).toHaveText('Success');
    await page.close();
    await use({username, password});
  }, {scope: 'worker'}],
  page: async ({page, account}, use) => {
    await page.goto('/signin');
    await page.getByLabel('User Name').fill(account.username);
    await page.getByLabel('Password').fill(account.password);
    await page.getByText('Sign in').click();
    await use(page);
  },
});

export {expect} from '@playwright/test';
```

scope: 'worker' creates fixture once per worker process. workerInfo.workerIndex provides unique index per worker. Useful for expensive setup (DB creation, auth) that should not repeat per test.

**Category:** Patterns
**URL:** https://playwright.dev/docs/test-fixtures

# Global Setup for Authentication

Authenticate once, reuse across all tests via storageState.

```typescript
// global-setup.ts
import {chromium, FullConfig} from '@playwright/test';

async function globalSetup(config: FullConfig) {
  const {baseURL, storageState} = config.projects[0].use;
  const browser = await chromium.launch();
  const page = await browser.newPage();
  await page.goto(baseURL!);
  await page.getByLabel('User Name').fill('user');
  await page.getByLabel('Password').fill('password');
  await page.getByText('Sign in').click();
  await page.context().storageState({path: storageState as string});
  await browser.close();
}

export default globalSetup;

// playwright.config.ts
export default defineConfig({
  globalSetup: require.resolve('./global-setup'),
  use: {
    baseURL: 'http://localhost:3000/',
    storageState: 'state.json',
  },
});
```

Tests automatically inherit authenticated state from storageState file. No re-login needed per test. globalTeardown also available for cleanup.

**Category:** Patterns
**URL:** https://playwright.dev/docs/test-global-setup-teardown

# Workers and Parallelism

Configure workers for parallel test execution.

```typescript
import {defineConfig} from '@playwright/test';

export default defineConfig({
  workers: 10,
  projects: [
    {name: 'parallel-tests'},
    {name: 'serial-tests', workers: 1},  // override for sequential
  ],
});
```

Worker isolation: each worker gets its own browser context. Use workerIndex for unique resources (DB users, ports). Worker-scoped fixtures initialize once per worker. fullyParallel: true runs tests within files in parallel too (default: tests in same file run sequentially).

Benefits: Tests run faster on multi-core machines. Resource isolation prevents test interference.

**Category:** Configuration
**URL:** https://playwright.dev/docs/test-parallel

# Worker Database Isolation

Isolate database changes per worker to prevent test interference.

```typescript
import {test as baseTest} from '@playwright/test';
import {
  createUserInTestDatabase,
  deleteUserFromTestDatabase,
} from './my-db-utils';

export const test = baseTest.extend<{}, {dbUserName: string}>({
  dbUserName: [async ({}, use) => {
    const userName = `user-${test.info().workerIndex}`;
    await createUserInTestDatabase(userName);
    await use(userName);
    await deleteUserFromTestDatabase(userName);
  }, {scope: 'worker'}],
});
```

Worker-scoped fixtures with workerIndex guarantee unique database users per parallel worker. Setup (create user) runs once per worker. Use passes fixture value to tests. Teardown (delete user) cleans up after all tests in worker complete.

**Category:** Patterns
**URL:** https://playwright.dev/docs/test-parallel

# Advanced API Mocking

Mock, modify, and replay network traffic.

```javascript
// Mock entire response
await page.route('*/**/api/v1/fruits', async route => {
  await route.fulfill({json: [{name:'Strawberry', id:21}]});
});

// Modify real response
await page.route('*/**/api/v1/fruits', async route => {
  const response = await route.fetch();
  const json = await response.json();
  json.push({name:'Loquat', id:100});
  await route.fulfill({response, json});
});

// HAR replay (record/playback)
await page.routeFromHAR('./hars/fruit.har', {
  url:'*/**/api/v1/fruits',
  update:false,
});

// WebSocket mock
await page.routeWebSocket('wss://example.com/ws', ws => {
  ws.onMessage(msg => {
    if (msg === 'request') ws.send('response');
  });
});

// Abort requests (block images)
await page.route('**/*.{png,jpg}', route => route.abort());
```

route.fulfill: return custom response. route.fetch: get real response to modify. route.abort: block request. routeFromHAR: replay recorded traffic (great for offline testing).

**Category:** Features
**URL:** https://playwright.dev/docs/mock
